Angina:

• Angina refers to the pain and discomfort in the chest area 
• It occurs due to a reduction in the supply of oxygen rich blood to the heart muscles
• There is a heavy and squeezing sensation in the chest
• The pain may extend to the jaw, neck, shoulder, back and arms

Symptoms to look for:

• Nausea
• Sweating
• Dizziness
• Fatigue
• Breathlessness
• Anxiety

Causes:

Blockage of blood arteries in the heart due to presence of cholesterol deposits, which obstructs the blood
supply to the heart muscles. This could occur due to,

• Smoking
• Diabetes
• High blood pressure
• Stress
• Unhealthy diet

